# Pinksync Starter

**Deaf-first. AI-powered. Future-ready.**

This is a hybrid **Next.js 14 + FastAPI** starter built for real-time, entrepreneurial, and rehabilitation workflows. Created by [Pinky Collie](https://mbtquniverse.com), this stack is built to support:

- Deaf-first API integration
- Vocational Rehabilitation (VR4Deaf)
- Job & Business development pipelines
- AI automation with scalable backend support

---

## How It Works

- **Frontend:** Next.js 14 (App Router)
- **Backend:** FastAPI (served under `/api/py`)
- **Vercel Production:** FastAPI runs as Python serverless functions alongside your React app.
- **Local Development:** FastAPI runs on `127.0.0.1:8000`, proxied via `next.config.js` rewrites.

---

## Folder Structure

/
├── app/                  # Next.js App Router
├── api/                  # FastAPI backend (Python)
│   ├── deaf.py           # Deaf-first endpoints
│   ├── job.py            # Job readiness APIs
│   ├── business.py       # Business startup APIs
│   ├── vr4deaf.py        # Vocational Rehab for Deaf
├── models/               # Pydantic schemas
├── services/             # Business logic modules
├── auth/                 # Authentication + token mgmt
├── utils/                # Helper functions/utilities
├── database/             # Database connection + queries
├── routers/              # FastAPI route includes
├── public/               # Static assets (Next.js)
├── main.py               # FastAPI entry point
├── next.config.js        # Rewrite rules for dev/prod
├── requirements.txt      # Python dependencies
├── package.json          # Node.js dependencies

---

## Getting Started

Clone and run locally:

```bash
npx create-next-app pinksync --example "https://github.com/digitros/nextjs-fastapi"
cd pinksync

# Set up Python backend
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# Install frontend and backend dependencies
npm install
pip install -r requirements.txt

# Run dev servers
npm run dev

	•	Open http://localhost:3000 for your app.
	•	FastAPI runs on http://127.0.0.1:8000.

⸻

Deployment on Vercel

Just connect your repo and Vercel will auto-detect the Next.js frontend and Python API functions in /api. No extra configuration needed.

⸻

